WEBVTT

00:05.255 --> 00:07.090
[horse whinnies]

00:11.678 --> 00:12.887
[horse nickers]

00:16.182 --> 00:18.268
♪ I'm gonna ride ♪

00:18.351 --> 00:20.270
♪ I'm riding free ♪

00:20.353 --> 00:22.397
♪ So come along, let's go along ♪

00:22.480 --> 00:24.441
♪ Come on a journey with me ♪

00:24.524 --> 00:26.484
♪ Voy a montar ♪

00:26.568 --> 00:28.653
♪ Salir de aquí ♪

00:28.737 --> 00:30.739
♪ As long as I am here with you ♪

00:30.822 --> 00:33.033
♪ I feel the spirit within me ♪

00:33.116 --> 00:34.409
♪ Yeah ♪

00:35.118 --> 00:36.536
♪ Yeah ♪

00:37.162 --> 00:38.663
♪ Yeah ♪

00:46.963 --> 00:48.923
[crows cawing]

00:50.967 --> 00:52.969
[upbeat country music playing]

00:54.512 --> 00:56.431
I didn't know a band was coming to town.

00:56.514 --> 00:58.141
Maybe there will be a dance.

00:59.100 --> 01:01.311
[gasps] That's no band! Look!

01:02.854 --> 01:04.105
[music continues]

01:04.981 --> 01:05.982
Hey, girls!

01:06.066 --> 01:08.318
How do you like the new gramophone, huh?

01:08.401 --> 01:09.652
I just got it in.

01:09.736 --> 01:12.197
If we bought it,
we could have dance parties in the barn.

01:12.280 --> 01:14.407
And I could finally learn the paso doble.

01:14.491 --> 01:16.785
Whoa! We can't afford this.

01:16.868 --> 01:19.245
[sighs] Adios, paso doble.

01:19.537 --> 01:22.332
Sure, we can afford it.
All we need is some extra money.

01:23.750 --> 01:26.836
-Where can we get some extra money?
-We could get part-time jobs.

01:26.920 --> 01:28.630
Yes! Winthrop, do you need any--

01:28.713 --> 01:30.298
No! Not again.

01:31.758 --> 01:33.468
[Lucky] There's got to be
a way to do this.

01:34.719 --> 01:35.845
Never again.

01:36.346 --> 01:38.389
Maybe Turo could use a junior blacksmith.

01:38.473 --> 01:40.099
Or Althea could use a bellhop.

01:40.183 --> 01:42.143
-Or maybe-- [yells]
-[coin rattles]

01:43.853 --> 01:45.313
...the crows will pay for it.

01:46.022 --> 01:48.191
-[horses snort]
-Um... Abigail?

01:50.026 --> 01:52.403
Abigail, why is money falling
from the sky on you?

01:52.654 --> 01:54.364
-The crows.
-[crows cawing]

01:56.699 --> 01:57.534
Remember?

01:59.077 --> 02:00.453
I told you all about it.

02:00.537 --> 02:02.664
-No, you didn't.
-Yes, I did.

02:02.747 --> 02:05.125
I told you and you said,
"I love the crows!"

02:05.208 --> 02:07.836
And then you hopped on
your unicycle and flew up into the...

02:08.461 --> 02:11.381
Oh, it might have been a dream.

02:11.464 --> 02:14.509
[sighs] Abigail, why are crows
dropping coins on you?

02:14.801 --> 02:16.803
Not just coins, all kinds of things.

02:16.886 --> 02:19.597
Sometimes it's bottle caps,
sometimes a thimble...

02:19.681 --> 02:21.391
Ooh! Or a shiny wire.

02:21.474 --> 02:22.892
Maybe start at the beginning.

02:23.393 --> 02:24.394
[sighs]

02:24.477 --> 02:27.105
Well, last week I saw
a bunch of hungry crows in my yard,

02:27.188 --> 02:28.398
so I gave them some bread.

02:28.481 --> 02:30.733
They came back the next day,
so I gave them pie.

02:30.817 --> 02:34.529
I've been feeding them every night since,
and they give me presents to say thanks.

02:34.612 --> 02:37.824
They're so sweet! I just never know
what they're gonna give me next.

02:37.907 --> 02:39.325
-[crow cawing]
-See?

02:40.493 --> 02:42.912
Thank you, Mister, or Miss, or Mrs. Crow!

02:42.996 --> 02:44.414
[crows cawing]

02:44.497 --> 02:47.208
Hey, maybe we could sell this
to buy the record player.

02:47.292 --> 02:48.376
[gasps] Uh...

02:48.459 --> 02:51.129
-Abigail, I've seen that watch before.
-[footsteps]

02:51.212 --> 02:52.797
-It belongs to--
-[man] Sheriff!

02:52.881 --> 02:54.215
There's a thief in town!

02:54.299 --> 02:56.467
My daddy's gold pocket watch, stolen!

02:56.551 --> 03:00.471
-Whoa, whoa, whoa. Slow down, Mr. Grayson.
-I've got no intention of slowing down.

03:00.555 --> 03:03.224
That watch has been
in my family for generations!

03:03.308 --> 03:04.767
Oh, no! Oh, no!

03:04.851 --> 03:06.895
I stole Mr. Grayson's pocket watch!

03:06.978 --> 03:08.521
Abigail, it's fine.

03:08.605 --> 03:11.065
Let's just take the watch over
and explain what happened.

03:11.149 --> 03:14.402
After all, he and I are on
not-terrible terms after we--

03:14.485 --> 03:15.737
No, I don't care who did this.

03:15.820 --> 03:18.531
I want them prosecuted
to the fullest extent of the law.

03:18.615 --> 03:19.616
You hear me?

03:20.158 --> 03:22.702
Now, Mr. Grayson, without a suspect--

03:22.785 --> 03:24.203
I don't care what their excuse is!

03:24.662 --> 03:26.331
I want them to rot in jail.

03:26.414 --> 03:28.791
-[Abigail whimpers]
-Hm... New plan.

03:29.542 --> 03:33.046
We'll sneak over to Grayson's ranch
tonight and leave it on his doorknob.

03:33.129 --> 03:36.299
He'll get his watch back, and we can
all pretend this never happened.

03:36.382 --> 03:38.134
But what if he catches us?

03:38.218 --> 03:41.054
[scoffs] We've snuck onto
his property loads of times.

03:41.137 --> 03:42.931
Trust me, we're not gonna get caught.

03:43.181 --> 03:44.307
-Caught you!
-[gasps]

03:44.390 --> 03:46.059
Bold as brass.

03:46.142 --> 03:49.020
Stealing my watch
and coming back for more? Give me that!

03:49.103 --> 03:50.730
I didn't steal it! A crow did!

03:50.813 --> 03:52.190
And then he gave it to me.

03:52.273 --> 03:55.485
How much hogwash
are you fixing to sell me, girlie?

03:55.568 --> 03:57.320
Abigail's telling the truth.

03:57.403 --> 04:00.406
She would never steal
from you... or anyone!

04:00.490 --> 04:03.451
Well, Abigail and you other two

04:03.534 --> 04:05.370
can tell your story to the judge!

04:05.453 --> 04:06.454
-Ow!
-Huh?

04:07.538 --> 04:08.957
[crows cawing]

04:09.040 --> 04:10.541
[Lucky] Ha! See? See?

04:10.625 --> 04:12.502
She's not lying. It's the crows!

04:12.752 --> 04:13.753
Now, go on, get!

04:14.295 --> 04:15.505
[crow squawks]

04:15.588 --> 04:17.340
Crows, fly away!

04:17.423 --> 04:19.425
-[squawking]
-Fly away!

04:19.968 --> 04:21.386
[gasps]

04:21.761 --> 04:23.263
[both gasp]

04:23.346 --> 04:24.764
You broke my window.

04:24.847 --> 04:26.391
That's theft and vandalism!

04:26.683 --> 04:28.017
That was an accident!

04:28.101 --> 04:29.894
You were hurting the crows.

04:29.978 --> 04:32.814
That's a $15 window,
and you're responsible.

04:32.897 --> 04:33.898
You all are!

04:33.982 --> 04:36.192
But I don't have any money.

04:36.276 --> 04:37.277
Oh, you can't pay?

04:37.360 --> 04:39.862
-Then I'll be calling the sheriff, girlie.
-[Abigail] Wait!

04:40.238 --> 04:42.699
There's got to be
something else we can do!

04:43.116 --> 04:44.117
Hm.

04:45.118 --> 04:47.996
I suppose you three can work it off.

04:48.079 --> 04:50.039
A week of work at $1 a day each,

04:50.123 --> 04:52.208
you'll have paid for that window.

04:52.292 --> 04:53.626
That's a square deal.

04:53.710 --> 04:55.712
Maybe I'll forget about you
taking my watch.

04:55.795 --> 04:57.463
-But... But....
-A whole week?

04:57.880 --> 04:59.841
You are either in that yard

04:59.924 --> 05:02.385
at nine o'clock tomorrow, ready to work,

05:02.468 --> 05:05.096
or I'll be at your house at 9:30

05:05.179 --> 05:06.306
with the sheriff.

05:06.389 --> 05:07.348
[girls gasp]

05:08.057 --> 05:09.183
Nighty-night.

05:11.352 --> 05:12.562
[Lucky] This is terrible!

05:12.895 --> 05:15.315
Now we'll never be able
to get that record player.

05:15.398 --> 05:16.941
-[crows cawing]
-Ooh! Toffee.

05:17.734 --> 05:19.319
[mumbles] Maybe it won't be too bad.

05:20.153 --> 05:23.114
[scoffs] You're right, Abigail.
It won't be "too bad."

05:23.197 --> 05:24.198
It will be worse!

05:24.282 --> 05:26.242
-[Spirit neighs]
-I don't know.

05:26.326 --> 05:28.328
[swallows] Everyone hates crows,

05:28.411 --> 05:29.787
but I was nice to them,

05:29.871 --> 05:31.622
and now look how nice they are to me.

05:31.706 --> 05:33.708
What does that have to do with anything?

05:33.791 --> 05:35.793
Maybe Grayson is only mean

05:35.877 --> 05:38.337
because no one has ever
been nice to him before.

05:38.421 --> 05:42.091
And I think if he knew that we were
his friends, he'd be nice, too.

05:44.635 --> 05:46.679
But... we're not his friends.

05:46.763 --> 05:48.681
Or are we?

05:48.765 --> 05:50.433
No, we're not.

05:50.516 --> 05:52.143
Not yet.

05:52.894 --> 05:54.062
[Pru] Not ever!

05:54.145 --> 05:55.229
Abigail!

05:56.773 --> 05:57.774
[Lucky] Bye, Dad.

05:58.149 --> 06:00.109
I'm off to work at Grayson's.

06:00.693 --> 06:02.570
Is it still work if I'm not getting paid?

06:02.653 --> 06:04.072
[Spirit nickers]

06:07.992 --> 06:09.202
[grunts]

06:16.042 --> 06:17.668
[foot-tapping continues]

06:25.093 --> 06:26.094
[yawns]

06:26.803 --> 06:28.221
[grunting]

06:30.056 --> 06:31.599
Y'all are late!

06:32.058 --> 06:33.392
-[stammers]
-Ahem!

06:34.852 --> 06:35.853
Let's get started.

06:35.937 --> 06:38.689
The barn's got loose shingles,
the garden needs weeding,

06:38.773 --> 06:42.735
I want that back lot over yonder
cleared of junk, the deck needs washing,

06:42.819 --> 06:45.780
there's some big spiderwebs
in the stalls that need sweeping.

06:46.114 --> 06:47.990
And that should last you till lunch,

06:48.491 --> 06:50.326
which I ain't providing.

06:51.202 --> 06:52.662
Can do, Mr. Grayson!

06:52.745 --> 06:53.746
These are for you,

06:54.122 --> 06:56.582
to commemorate our first day
on the job together.

06:57.667 --> 06:58.876
Well, all right, then.

06:59.752 --> 07:00.753
Get to work!

07:01.921 --> 07:03.798
And don't hurt yourselves none.

07:04.173 --> 07:07.343
Though ending up in the hospital
is better than ending up in the hoosegow.

07:09.720 --> 07:10.930
I think that went well.

07:11.347 --> 07:13.599
I bet nobody has ever
given him flowers before.

07:14.308 --> 07:15.685
I bet you're right.

07:15.768 --> 07:17.770
Come on, Abigail. Get to work.

07:18.980 --> 07:19.981
[giggles]

07:20.523 --> 07:21.941
[chickens clucking]

07:22.024 --> 07:23.651
[girls grunting]

07:24.735 --> 07:25.862
[Abigail] Come on!

07:29.240 --> 07:30.867
[horse neighs]

07:32.034 --> 07:33.369
Hyah! Go on!

07:35.830 --> 07:39.500
Hyah! Ain't you ever gonna
learn to back up? Go on!

07:39.584 --> 07:42.253
-[whinnies]
-I ought to sell you, you useless nag!

07:42.336 --> 07:43.963
[whinnying continues]

07:51.512 --> 07:52.930
Well, there, you big stupid!

07:53.014 --> 07:54.390
[horse nickers]

07:54.724 --> 07:56.017
Go on, back to work!

07:56.934 --> 07:58.269
Poor Xerxes.

07:58.352 --> 08:00.229
He must hate feeling trapped in there.

08:00.313 --> 08:02.732
I wish he knew Spirit's
hopping trick from the circus

08:02.815 --> 08:04.233
so that he could turn in that chute.

08:04.317 --> 08:06.277
[gasps] I bet Spirit and I
could teach him!

08:06.360 --> 08:08.321
Ooh! Mr. Grayson's taking a break.

08:08.404 --> 08:09.822
This is my chance!

08:10.323 --> 08:12.617
-This is my chance, too!
-[sighs]

08:12.867 --> 08:16.370
Or we could just focus on
the stuff Grayson wants us to do.

08:22.919 --> 08:24.337
[gargles and swallows]

08:27.632 --> 08:28.633
What's that?

08:28.716 --> 08:30.760
My famous turkey on home-baked rye,

08:30.843 --> 08:32.094
with extra mustard,

08:32.178 --> 08:33.596
the way it ought to be.

08:33.679 --> 08:36.140
I thought you'd be hungry
after working all morning long.

08:37.266 --> 08:38.684
[grunts]

08:41.854 --> 08:42.939
Mm.

08:44.023 --> 08:45.816
Get... Get back to work, you hear?

08:47.276 --> 08:48.277
Will do!

08:50.279 --> 08:51.447
Hey.

08:51.531 --> 08:52.949
Hey, Xerxes.

08:53.032 --> 08:55.034
Watch this. Spirit!

09:03.251 --> 09:04.377
Watch, Xerxes.

09:07.338 --> 09:09.257
Spirit, hop! Hop!

09:11.300 --> 09:12.343
[neighs]

09:13.594 --> 09:15.137
How would you like to learn that, boy?

09:15.221 --> 09:16.931
-[Xerxes whinnies]
-Spirit!

09:17.223 --> 09:18.432
You stop that!

09:19.141 --> 09:20.935
Can you balance on your back legs?

09:21.018 --> 09:22.228
[Boomerang neighs]

09:23.354 --> 09:24.355
[whinnies]

09:24.438 --> 09:26.857
-[clattering]
-[snorts]

09:26.941 --> 09:28.985
[laughs] Almost, Boomerang.

09:29.485 --> 09:30.987
See? Can you try, too?

09:32.613 --> 09:34.156
[neighs]

09:34.699 --> 09:36.367
Yay! You almost did it!

09:36.450 --> 09:37.868
We'll keep practicing,

09:37.952 --> 09:39.787
as long as Grayson doesn't catch us.

09:41.581 --> 09:43.082
[grumbling] Stupid Grayson.

09:43.165 --> 09:44.834
I didn't break any windows.

09:44.917 --> 09:46.627
Crows didn't bring me anything.

09:46.711 --> 09:48.629
Why am I the only one
doing work around here?

09:48.713 --> 09:49.547
[sighs]

09:50.172 --> 09:51.591
[snoring]

09:53.801 --> 09:55.011
[gasps]

09:58.222 --> 09:59.223
What are you doing?

09:59.307 --> 10:01.976
I love a nap after a big sandwich.

10:02.435 --> 10:03.936
[gasps] And so do you!

10:04.228 --> 10:06.147
-We have so much in common.
-[groans]

10:06.230 --> 10:08.065
-[gasps]
-Now, get back to work!

10:08.941 --> 10:10.651
-[screams]
-Keep away from me, Blondie!

10:11.485 --> 10:12.737
Enough monkeying around!

10:12.820 --> 10:14.614
Now, you get these chores done

10:14.697 --> 10:17.742
and be back tomorrow
bright and early for more.

10:22.413 --> 10:23.998
If you look nice on the outside,

10:24.081 --> 10:25.750
you feel nice on the inside.

10:27.543 --> 10:29.170
[crickets chirping]

10:35.301 --> 10:37.970
Well, I'm thinking
you got nothing, Conway.

10:38.471 --> 10:39.805
Nothing but an empty hand.

10:39.889 --> 10:41.766
[others laugh]

10:41.849 --> 10:44.268
You heard me? I called you.

10:44.352 --> 10:46.020
[laughter continues]

10:46.103 --> 10:47.229
Now, what is so funny?

10:47.313 --> 10:48.648
[stifled laughter]

10:50.358 --> 10:51.942
You sure look pretty tonight, Grayson.

10:52.026 --> 10:54.278
-[laughter continues]
-[groans]

10:55.863 --> 10:56.989
[yells]

10:58.908 --> 11:00.493
I don't want none of you -

11:00.576 --> 11:02.328
and by that I mean you, Blondie -

11:02.411 --> 11:04.413
touching my things or going in my house

11:04.497 --> 11:06.415
or trying to do nice things for me!

11:07.458 --> 11:10.294
Oh. Does this count as nice?

11:10.544 --> 11:12.463
What in the world?

11:12.546 --> 11:15.841
I stayed up all night to make sure
your tootsies stay toasty.

11:15.925 --> 11:17.551
Warm toes make a warm heart.

11:17.635 --> 11:19.845
And my name is Abigail, not "Blondie."

11:19.929 --> 11:22.973
But if we're giving each other nicknames,
how about I call you "Cricket,"

11:23.057 --> 11:24.266
'cause you've got long legs?

11:24.350 --> 11:27.228
[grunts] Cozy socks
ain't getting you no favors!

11:27.311 --> 11:28.437
Now, get to work!

11:29.522 --> 11:32.066
Grayson sure is getting
his money's worth out of us.

11:32.149 --> 11:34.402
[sighs] You mean "his no-money's worth."

11:34.485 --> 11:37.905
Don't worry, PALs. The crows weren't
my friends on the first day, either.

11:37.988 --> 11:39.198
Grayson will come around.

11:39.281 --> 11:40.574
♪ La-la, la-la-la ♪

11:43.119 --> 11:44.120
[blows gently]

11:46.580 --> 11:48.874
Tell me what life was like
when you were a little boy.

11:48.958 --> 11:50.584
Well, I... No!

11:50.668 --> 11:52.378
Now, get out of here! Scat!

11:52.920 --> 11:54.505
♪ La-la-la, la-la-la ♪

11:55.589 --> 11:58.426
♪ Oh, I got a friend that's a Grayson ♪

11:58.509 --> 12:01.220
♪ He's a funny old friend indeed ♪

12:01.303 --> 12:03.722
♪ My new best friend is a Grayson ♪

12:03.806 --> 12:06.392
♪ Oh, he's the pal for me ♪

12:06.475 --> 12:08.561
-[coughs and splutters]
-Oh, hi, there, Cricket.

12:10.187 --> 12:11.480
What have you done to my porch?

12:12.231 --> 12:15.651
I made it a fine place
for sipping some sweet tea

12:15.734 --> 12:17.611
and listening to the whip-poor-wills.

12:17.695 --> 12:19.405
Twit-twoo! Twit-twoo!

12:19.488 --> 12:20.489
Twit-twoo!

12:20.573 --> 12:22.700
-Twit-twoo! Twit-twoo!
-[yells]

12:22.783 --> 12:24.952
-You're welcome!
-I got errands.

12:25.035 --> 12:27.705
Now, get that barn mucked out
before I get back.

12:28.622 --> 12:30.666
I think I'm winning him over.

12:30.749 --> 12:32.126
What makes you think that?

12:32.209 --> 12:33.627
He's wearing my socks!

12:34.462 --> 12:36.672
Well, I think I'm winning Xerxes over.

12:36.755 --> 12:39.300
I wonder if he remembers
everything I taught him yesterday.

12:40.801 --> 12:42.428
[groans]

12:42.720 --> 12:46.390
I am not mucking out
these stables all by myself!

12:47.558 --> 12:48.684
[grunts]

12:52.730 --> 12:53.856
[grunts]

12:55.191 --> 12:57.693
[Lucky] Come on, Xerxes.
You know this. Remember?

12:57.776 --> 12:58.986
[Xerxes neighs]

12:59.570 --> 13:01.030
Rear up and hop around.

13:02.323 --> 13:03.365
[nickers]

13:03.449 --> 13:05.075
[Xerxes whinnies]

13:06.702 --> 13:08.078
[nickers]

13:08.162 --> 13:09.413
[grunts]

13:09.872 --> 13:10.956
[neighs]

13:11.040 --> 13:12.875
That's how you do it! Now hop!

13:14.835 --> 13:16.128
[nickers]

13:17.421 --> 13:18.714
[neighs]

13:19.215 --> 13:21.008
[sighs] Come on, Spirit. Please help?

13:27.431 --> 13:28.724
[nickers]

13:29.225 --> 13:30.309
[nickers]

13:32.895 --> 13:34.522
[neighing]

13:37.566 --> 13:39.818
You can do it, Xerxes.
Try it one more time.

13:40.152 --> 13:41.153
[snorts]

13:42.363 --> 13:43.781
[whinnying]

13:46.116 --> 13:47.618
-Yeah!
-[neighs]

13:47.701 --> 13:48.702
[nickers]

13:48.786 --> 13:49.995
[neighs]

13:50.371 --> 13:53.457
See, Pru? With enough effort,
you can get through to anyone.

13:53.541 --> 13:56.919
And I'm gonna make sure Grayson knows
what a special horse Xerxes is.

14:01.173 --> 14:02.007
[gasps]

14:04.134 --> 14:05.302
Oh, Mr. Grayson!

14:05.386 --> 14:06.971
We have some amazing news.

14:07.054 --> 14:09.682
-Xerxes learned how to--
-Get away from him!

14:09.765 --> 14:12.351
Mr. Grayson, you have to see
what Lucky taught Xerxes.

14:12.434 --> 14:15.896
-I taught him a trick that will make it--
-He don't need to learn nothing from you!

14:15.980 --> 14:17.690
He's already a fine cutting horse,

14:17.773 --> 14:19.608
and that's all he needs to know!

14:19.692 --> 14:20.776
But Lucky showed him how--

14:20.860 --> 14:22.111
Now, I've been gone two hours,

14:22.194 --> 14:24.738
so I guess that's two more hours
of work which you owe me

14:24.822 --> 14:25.990
you should have been doing.

14:26.073 --> 14:27.741
-[cawing]
-What in the...? Not again!

14:29.410 --> 14:30.619
[Abigail gasps]

14:32.037 --> 14:33.706
-[yelling]
-[whinnying]

14:34.123 --> 14:35.124
-No!
-Oh, no!

14:35.207 --> 14:36.208
[gasps]

14:37.960 --> 14:39.962
-[grumbles]
-[Lucky] We got 'em!

14:41.714 --> 14:43.340
[whinnying]

14:48.721 --> 14:49.930
[Pru] We're ready, Lucky.

14:50.764 --> 14:51.891
OK.

14:51.974 --> 14:53.225
Let's do it, Spirit.

14:54.226 --> 14:55.853
[Spirit neighs]

14:55.936 --> 14:57.855
[whinnying]

14:57.938 --> 14:59.023
[grunts]

14:59.815 --> 15:01.066
[whinnies]

15:01.567 --> 15:03.402
-[Boomerang snorts]
-[whinnying]

15:04.820 --> 15:06.238
-[Pru] Gotcha.
-[Abigail] Yeah!

15:07.698 --> 15:10.034
-We did it!
-[Grayson] You sure did.

15:13.412 --> 15:16.457
We're sorry, Mr. Grayson.
We'll get the fence right back up.

15:16.999 --> 15:19.043
At least we got your watch.

15:19.126 --> 15:21.587
We really are sorry.
Friends mess up sometimes.

15:21.670 --> 15:25.883
-But as long as you forgive each other--
-Friends? D-Did you just say "friends"?

15:26.759 --> 15:29.428
-Abigail, let's go muck out the barn.
-No, no, no.

15:29.970 --> 15:31.639
She should stay and hear this.

15:32.139 --> 15:35.225
Little girl, we aren't friends.

15:35.309 --> 15:37.728
I don't want to be friends with you.

15:38.729 --> 15:40.856
Well... not yet.

15:41.482 --> 15:42.775
Not ever!

15:42.858 --> 15:44.985
I'd never be friends

15:45.069 --> 15:47.613
with such a silly little towheaded,

15:47.696 --> 15:49.823
know-nothing chatterbox!

15:50.199 --> 15:52.576
So you can keep your silly songs

15:52.660 --> 15:54.536
and your stale sandwiches

15:54.620 --> 15:56.413
and your scratchy socks to yourself.

15:56.997 --> 15:57.998
I don't like 'em...

15:58.624 --> 16:00.501
and I don't like you.

16:01.377 --> 16:03.253
It just takes time.

16:03.629 --> 16:04.755
You'll see.

16:04.838 --> 16:06.298
The crows used to be mean, too,

16:06.382 --> 16:08.634
but I didn't give up, and now they're--

16:08.717 --> 16:10.386
[laughs]

16:10.886 --> 16:12.930
Girl, you're certifiable!

16:13.347 --> 16:15.349
Listen to what I am saying.

16:15.432 --> 16:17.810
I ain't never gonna change.

16:17.893 --> 16:19.144
Not for you.

16:19.812 --> 16:21.105
You ain't worth it.

16:24.733 --> 16:25.776
All right.

16:25.859 --> 16:26.944
I understand.

16:28.612 --> 16:30.739
-Let's go, boy.
-Where are you going?

16:31.407 --> 16:32.408
Hey!

16:33.409 --> 16:34.451
You get back here!

16:34.827 --> 16:36.286
You got a fence to fix!

16:37.579 --> 16:39.540
You three better be back here tomorrow,

16:39.623 --> 16:42.501
or Blondie there is gonna be a jailbird!

16:42.584 --> 16:43.669
You all are!

16:48.966 --> 16:50.384
[apples thudding]

16:56.640 --> 16:59.810
[Lucky] Aw. Look, Abigail.
He's trying to cheer you up.

17:00.310 --> 17:02.479
[sighs] There's no cheering me up.

17:02.563 --> 17:03.731
You were right, Pru.

17:03.814 --> 17:05.733
Grayson isn't a good person at heart.

17:05.816 --> 17:07.735
He's just bad, bad, bad.

17:07.818 --> 17:09.570
Abigail, this isn't like you.

17:09.653 --> 17:11.572
Well, maybe it should be.

17:11.655 --> 17:13.657
Maybe I should just be a sad Abigail.

17:14.116 --> 17:16.285
Maybe like a Sabigail?

17:16.785 --> 17:17.870
No, Pru.

17:17.953 --> 17:19.204
Like a sad Abigail.

17:20.247 --> 17:23.292
I believed with all my heart
that everyone has some good inside.

17:23.792 --> 17:25.377
But if I'm wrong about Grayson,

17:25.461 --> 17:27.129
what else am I wrong about?

17:27.212 --> 17:29.048
You can't judge anything by Grayson.

17:29.131 --> 17:30.340
He's mean on purpose.

17:30.424 --> 17:33.510
We don't need to make friends with him,
we just need to get the work done.

17:33.594 --> 17:35.554
Then you'll never have
to talk to him again.

17:35.637 --> 17:37.056
I can't go back there!

17:37.139 --> 17:39.641
I guess I'll just go
turn myself in to the sheriff.

17:39.975 --> 17:41.894
A felon, me!

17:42.394 --> 17:43.395
[sighs]

17:44.438 --> 17:47.024
Wait! Pru and I will do your share
of the chores for you.

17:47.107 --> 17:48.817
Oh, are you gonna help now?

17:49.610 --> 17:50.736
Don't worry, Abigail.

17:50.819 --> 17:53.405
-We're going to take care of everything.
-Thanks, PALs.

17:53.947 --> 17:56.492
I guess I'll go raid Snips's candy stash.

17:56.575 --> 17:58.619
Will sugar even still be sweet?

17:59.078 --> 17:59.912
[sighs]

18:02.039 --> 18:04.291
Grayson had his chance to make a friend.

18:04.374 --> 18:06.168
Instead, he's made an enemy.

18:06.251 --> 18:07.503
Two enemies!

18:08.003 --> 18:09.421
And we're gonna make him pay.

18:09.505 --> 18:11.507
What are we gonna do, huh? Yell at him?

18:11.590 --> 18:13.509
Give him the silent treatment? Yeah!

18:13.592 --> 18:15.177
Something way worse.

18:15.260 --> 18:18.430
We're gonna make him feel as miserable
as he made Abigail feel.

18:18.514 --> 18:21.016
And what really annoys Grayson?

18:21.100 --> 18:22.351
-Abigail!
-Friendship!

18:23.102 --> 18:24.353
-Abigail!
-Friendship!

18:25.229 --> 18:26.230
Both!

18:27.147 --> 18:29.316
If we really want
to get under Grayson's skin,

18:29.399 --> 18:31.235
we just have to do what Abigail would do.

18:31.318 --> 18:32.152
Yeah.

18:33.445 --> 18:36.406
But... what would Abigail do?

18:37.366 --> 18:38.450
[Lucky] Hm.

18:39.284 --> 18:42.287
I keep trying to picture bunnies,
but they aren't telling me a plan.

18:43.080 --> 18:45.541
-Should we go home and make a pie?
-Maybe this will help.

18:45.916 --> 18:47.167
[grunts]

18:47.251 --> 18:49.795
Oh! Nope, just getting dizzy.

18:50.379 --> 18:52.172
-Any ideas, Spirit?
-[snorts]

18:56.009 --> 18:58.637
-Anything?
-No. But thanks, boy.

18:59.054 --> 19:00.305
Come on, think!

19:00.389 --> 19:03.308
What is something Abigail loves
more than anything else in the world?

19:03.392 --> 19:06.645
Something big with songs
and dancing and treats and...

19:07.187 --> 19:08.188
I've got it!

19:10.107 --> 19:11.608
[yawning]

19:12.192 --> 19:14.194
What? What in tarnation?

19:14.278 --> 19:15.696
[whinnying]

19:16.655 --> 19:18.282
-Happy Birthday!
-[horns honking]

19:18.365 --> 19:20.951
-[gasps]
-We're having a party for you, Cricket!

19:21.034 --> 19:23.871
A super-sweetest happy-birthday party!

19:23.954 --> 19:26.206
Well, today ain't my birthday.

19:26.290 --> 19:27.416
That's OK!

19:27.499 --> 19:30.419
We've missed so many,
we've got to catch up for every one!

19:30.502 --> 19:34.256
And every catch-up birthday starts with
the "Catch-up Birthday Song"!

19:34.339 --> 19:36.967
♪ Oh, tomorrow's a tomato
And yesterday's a yam ♪

19:37.050 --> 19:39.720
♪ But if you miss your birthday
That puts you in a jam ♪

19:40.679 --> 19:43.515
[splutters] OK, that is...
that is enough, now!

19:43.599 --> 19:44.766
[laughs] No way!

19:44.850 --> 19:46.935
We've got about 30 more
birthdays to catch up on.

