19:57.613 --> 20:00.407
♪ Oh, tomorrow's a tomato
And yesterday's a yam ♪

20:00.490 --> 20:02.951
♪ But if you miss your birthday
That puts you in a jam ♪

20:03.035 --> 20:05.579
Stop! I said enough!

20:05.913 --> 20:08.415
It was bad enough with Blondie
yakking at me all the time.

20:08.498 --> 20:10.918
I can't take it double, so cut it out!

20:11.001 --> 20:12.669
Not until you apologize to Abigail.

20:12.753 --> 20:13.921
[Abigail] It's OK, Lucky.

20:15.172 --> 20:18.217
-[Pru] Abigail, what are you doing here?
-I had to come back.

20:18.508 --> 20:21.386
I wasn't going to make my friends
do all the work by themselves.

20:21.470 --> 20:23.972
Yeah? Well, you're just in time to leave.

20:24.056 --> 20:26.099
Now, get off my property, the lot of you!

20:26.516 --> 20:28.268
Xerxes and I have got work to do.

20:28.352 --> 20:30.979
We can't leave.
We still owe you for the window.

20:31.063 --> 20:34.274
And we're gonna be working right here
by your side till we pay it off.

20:34.358 --> 20:36.526
Yeah, working and singing

20:36.610 --> 20:38.111
and smiling and...

20:38.612 --> 20:39.613
and...

20:39.696 --> 20:41.823
-Puppet shows?
-Yes!

20:41.907 --> 20:44.952
We're going to do puppet shows
day and night till we pay off what we owe.

20:45.035 --> 20:47.162
Never mind! Never mind.
The window was an accident.

20:47.246 --> 20:48.830
You don't owe me nothing.

20:48.914 --> 20:49.998
[Lucky gasps]

20:50.874 --> 20:52.084
Wait a minute.

20:52.167 --> 20:53.669
If the window was an accident,

20:53.752 --> 20:55.545
then it seems to me that you owe us

20:55.629 --> 20:56.880
for three days of labor.

20:58.173 --> 20:59.591
No, no. No, you see here--

20:59.675 --> 21:03.595
Abigail, don't you know a song
about fairness that you could teach us?

21:03.679 --> 21:04.763
Sure, I do!

21:04.846 --> 21:08.392
♪ A turtle and a turkey
Went to the turnip store ♪

21:08.475 --> 21:09.893
♪ They walked into the front and-- ♪

21:09.977 --> 21:11.478
-Fine! Take it!
-[gasps]

21:11.561 --> 21:13.647
Just get off my property
and don't come back.

21:13.730 --> 21:15.691
-[laughs] Yes!
-Yeah!

21:15.774 --> 21:16.775
Whoo!

21:17.150 --> 21:19.486
Let's go, PALs. Our work here is done.

21:19.569 --> 21:20.946
-[Spirit neighs]
-[Pru laughs]

21:21.029 --> 21:22.322
[Abigail] What just happened?

21:22.990 --> 21:25.450
We wanted to make Grayson pay
for how he treated you.

21:25.534 --> 21:27.077
Aw! That's OK.

21:27.160 --> 21:30.956
It doesn't matter if Grayson's nice,
because I'm nice, and that's what counts.

21:31.039 --> 21:33.333
Besides,
I don't need to be friends with him.

21:33.417 --> 21:35.544
I already have
the best friends in the world.

21:35.627 --> 21:37.045
-Ow!
-[crows cawing]

21:39.339 --> 21:40.757
You guys aren't too bad, either.

21:41.091 --> 21:43.093
You might not have
gotten through to Grayson,

21:43.176 --> 21:45.554
but it looks like Lucky
got through to Xerxes.

21:45.637 --> 21:48.598
Here we go, Xerxes.
I need one thing going right today.

21:49.224 --> 21:50.267
[nickers]

21:50.976 --> 21:52.602
-[whinnying]
-Whoa! Whoa!

21:52.686 --> 21:53.812
Hey! [laughs]

21:53.895 --> 21:56.648
How did you learn to do that,
you smart old thing?

21:56.732 --> 21:58.734
Good boy! Good, Xerxes!

21:58.817 --> 21:59.901
[laughs]

21:59.985 --> 22:03.363
Abigail, it worked! Grayson's being nice!

22:03.447 --> 22:05.824
I can't believe you actually changed him.

22:05.907 --> 22:08.368
Of course I did.
How could you have ever doubted me?

22:08.452 --> 22:10.454
[laughs] Let's go celebrate.

22:10.537 --> 22:12.664
[chuckles] And I know just how to do it.

22:12.748 --> 22:14.750
[horses whinnying]

22:17.794 --> 22:19.796
[mariachi music playing]

22:28.930 --> 22:30.348
[Chica Linda neighs]

22:30.807 --> 22:32.225
[Boomerang neighs]
